	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Ex 1_Exploring the Products API",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Endpoint",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "All products",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Single product",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products/1",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products",
								"1"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Limit products to 5",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products?limit=5&skip;=10",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products"
							],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "limit",
									"value": "5"
								},
								{
									"key": "skip;",
									"value": "10"
								}
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Search product",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"//Assertion\r",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
									"});\r",
									"pm.test(\"Product Array is not empty\", function () {\r",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.json().products).to.not.be.empty;\r",
									"});\r",
									"pm.test(\"All titles contain phone\", function () {\r",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.json().products).to.satisfy((products) => {\r",
									"        return products.every(product => product.title.toLowerCase().includes('phone'));\r",
									"    });\r",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"packages": {}
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products/search?q=phone",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products",
								"search"
							],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "q",
									"value": "phone"
								}
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "1. Send GET [https://dummyjson.com/products](https://dummyjson.com/products) — observe the response structure.\n    \n2. Send GET [https://dummyjson.com/products/1](https://dummyjson.com/products/1) — what fields does a single product have?\n    \n3. Add ?select=id,title,price,stock to the URL — verify only those fields return.\n    \n4. Try ?limit=5&skip;=10 — verify you get 5 products starting from the 11th.\n    \n5. Search for 'phone': GET [https://dummyjson.com/products/search?q=phone](https://dummyjson.com/products/search?q=phone)\n    \n6. Assert: status is 200, products array is not empty, all titles contain 'phone'.  \n    Goal: Goal: Understand GET requests, query parameters, and field selection.  \n    Exercise"
		},
		{
			"name": "Ex 2_Test Status Codes Systematically",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Response Time",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products/1",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products",
								"1"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Error Message",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products/99999",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products",
								"99999"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Neutral Integer",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products/0",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products",
								"0"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Negative ID",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products/-1",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products",
								"-1"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Non-numeric ID",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BaseURL}}/products/abc",
							"host": [
								"{{BaseURL}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"products",
								"abc"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "1. GET /products/1 ® expect 200. Capture response time.\n    \n2. GET /products/99999 ® expect 404. Read the error message.\n    \n3. GET /products/0 ® what happens? Is 0 a valid ID?\n    \n4. GET /products/-1 ® negative ID. What status code and message?\n    \n5. GET /products/abc ® non-numeric ID. What status code?\n    \n6. Document each result in a table: endpoint, expected code, actual code, notes.  \n    n Goal: Goal: Learn to test boundary and invalid inputs systematically."
		},
		{
			"name": "Ex 4_ Authentication Flow",
			"item": [
				{
